Good Afternoon Parents,

Due to severe weather resulting from Hurricane Marco, all classes, virtual learning, and offices will be closed Monday and Tuesday.

Crocker and Cohen: There will be no food distribution on Monday or Tuesday due to weather safety concerns. (School) will communicate out to families on the next food distribution date and times as soon as it is safe to resume operations.

Crocker and Cohen will resume all virtual classes on Wednesday, and Hoffman will resume in person classes on Wednesday. We continue to be in communication with local officials with respect to Hurricane Laura, and if severe weather continues beyond Tuesday, we will send school updates to families.

shared_text:
New Orleans College Prep Charter Schools
June 1 at 10:00 AM ¬∑

Don't forget! June 2nd is Give Nola Day.

What is GiveNOLA Day?

GiveNOLA Day, an initiative of the Greater New Orleans Foundation, is a one day online giving event. For 24 hours, everyone who loves our region can support their favorite local causes by donating to one or more of 700+ participating nonprofit organizations. Last year's event raised nearly $5.9 million from over 50,000 donations across the nation and around the world. This year, we hope to do even more!

For more information on donating to New Orleans College Prep, click on this link. https://www.givenola.org/nocp

Never have our nation‚Äôs teachers been more appreciated and seen as they work with providing continuity of care with our students from a distance. Monday-Name one thing you‚Äôve recently learned about the work your child/children‚Äôs teacher does.

post_text:
Good Morning/Evening Parents,

This is Kevin Word, principal at Crocker College Prep, calling with an important announcement.

As you know, Governor Edwards has now issued an order closing all Louisiana schools buildings for the remainder of the school year. While our school building may be closed for now, please know that online school WILL CONTINUE and our teachers will be teaching students in April and May until further notice.

Our Crocker employees are also working to establish final grading and promotion guidelines. Please know that in no way will your child be penalized for the school closure period. We will continue online instruction in April and May and do everything possible to cover any educational gaps for your child.

I will be back in contact with you soon as we receive updates from the state. Please take care and know that all of us at the school miss our students and stand ready to ensure that they remain on track for their educational needs.

Thank you!

This #JOY moment is brought to you by our Lawrence D. Crocker College Prep music department and Pre-Kindergarten team.
Our youngest scholars had an opportunity to explore hand percussion instruments. and even created their very own hand percussion instrument using cardboard and sandpaper. These future musicians even learned a few rhythms and can now clap and identify eighth/quarter notes and quarter rests with no problem!

Park at Cohen College Prep during Mardi Gras parades!

$25 parking pass includes all-day restroom passes for everyone in your vehicle and we‚Äôll have security on the lot at all times. We‚Äôre two blocks from the parade route! Enter lot from Baronne at Foucher. All proceeds benefit our students.

Available Friday, Feb 22 - Sunday, Feb 24 and Wednesday, Feb 27 - Tuesday, March 3. The lot opens two hours before the first parade and closes two hours after the end of the last parade crosses Louisiana.

Visit us online or call Cohen College Prep (504-335-0400) to reserve your spot! The lot fills up so get there early on the day of the parade or reserve a spot ahead of time! Cash only for day-of parking.

Special thanks to the Walter L Cohen Alumni Association who run parking operations each year!

The Historic New Orleans Collection (THNOC) has named Mariah Bledsoe, a Senior at Walter L. Cohen College Prep High School, a Spring 2019 Derven Scholar! Mariah will be mentored by education staff and will have the paid opportunity to work with staff from across THNOC to create and complete an original research project. This is a highly competitive program and only one student is selected each term. Congratulations, Mariah!
Way to go Cohen!!!! Small School, BIG Wins!!
#CohenCollegePrep #WaLoCo Orleans Parish School Board

It's #WaLoCoWednesday and this extra special feature is for Jakiara S. who takes advantage of allllll Cohen has to offer. She's a self-proclaimed social butterfly, but her social life never stands in the way of her academic pursuits. She is on the Principal's Honor Roll (All A's) and is preparing herself to become a criminal defense attorney. When asked what she enjoys most about Cohen, she responded, "That the adults here know I have the ability to do more and they push me to go above and beyond above my capabilities."
She comes from a long-line of Green Hornets and we're proud to have Jakiara continue our tradition of greatness! #iAmCohen #ChooseCohen #ThisIsCohen #GreatThingsHappenAtNOCP

It's Throwback Thursday, so we're reminiscing on Lawrence D. Crocker College Prep's trip to Loyola University New Orleans just a few weeks ago. During this trip, our 5th grade scholars had the opportunity to observe Loyola Chemistry students perform exciting science experiments. Our Crocker students even had a chance to to grade the college students!
Thank you Loyola University New Orleans: Forensic Chemistry Program for your partnership and the opportunity to bring science to life for our students! #nolaed #PrepforCollege #PrepforLife

post_text:
As a result of high performance in the 2017-18 school year. Hoffman Early Learning Center made the Louisiana State Department of Education Honor Roll for Birth to Three! Centers on this list provided high
quality instruction and care to the state's youngest learners, children birth through age three. This is significant because Louisiana serves far fewer economically disadvantaged children birth through age three, and early childhood sites typically score lower in performance categories related to these age groups. Congratulations to the entire Hoffman team! #Excellence

post_text: For this edition of #WaLoCoWednesday we're shouting out current Walter L. Cohen College Prep High School student, Kyle Delaney! Kyle is a graduating senior and is an extremely active Green Hornet! He is a member of the football team, basketball team, the National Honor Society, and is already taking college courses via our Bard Early College Program ( Bard Early College New Orleans ). post_text:
We are so proud of the Green Hornets Soccer Program! On Saturday, October 20th the team won the Crescent City Fall Championship !!! This is the first time in Walter L. Cohen's nearly 70 year history that the Green Hornets fielded a competitive soccer team.
The formation of the team has been a two-year process led by Cohen's Latinos Unidos student organization. These students created petitions and worked with the school's administration to make the team a reality. Please make a special effort to congratulate all of the student-athletes and coaching staff on an amazing season!!!
